he first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Picot was born in 1170, in Quy, Cambridgeshire, England, his father, Sir Aubrey Picot of Quy, was 25 and his mother, Matilda de Glanville, was 81. He married Mrs William Picot before 1194, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1218, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1170–1218":"1170–1218","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1164–1218":"1164–1218","–1185":"–1185","–1218":"–1218","–Female":"Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1194–1233":"1194–1233","1145–1185":"1145–1185","1089–1165":"1089–1165","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1145":"1145","1233":"1233","1089":"1089","before 1194":"enne 1194","1218":"1218","Quy, Waterbeach, &amp; Huntingfields in Boxworth, Cambridgeshire, England":"Waterbeach, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Quy, Cambridgeshire, England":"Quy, Cambridgeshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1170–1218":"1170–1218","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1164–1218":"1164–1218","–1185":"–1185","–1218":"–1218","–Female":"Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1194–1233":"